<objectXMLWrap>
               <did xmlns="urn:isbn:1-931666-22-9">
                  <unittitle>Hugo Weisgall Papers</unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1922-1997</unitdate>
                  <unitdate>1934 - 1997</unitdate>
                  <unitid>JPB 00-43</unitid>
                  <unitid>20266</unitid>
                  <origination>
                     <persname>Weisgall, Hugo</persname>
                  </origination>
                  <repository>
                     <corpname>The New York Public Library. Music Division.</corpname>
                     <address>
                        <addressline>New York Public Library for the Performing Arts, Dorothy and Lewis B. Cullman Center</addressline>
                        <addressline>40 Lincoln Center Plaza, New York, NY 10023-7498</addressline>
                     </address>
                  </repository>
                  <physdesc>
                     <extent>13.75</extent>
                     <extent>36 boxes</extent>
                  </physdesc>
                  <abstract>Papers documenting the career of the Czech-born American composer between the 1930s and the 1990s. Includes scores, libretti, posters, correspondence, clippings, programs, writings on music, financial documents and photographs.</abstract>
                  <langmaterial>Family letters in the correspondence series are mostly in German or Hungarian</langmaterial>
                  <langmaterial>English</langmaterial>
               </did>
            </objectXMLWrap>
